review_data: Reviewed in the United States on December 20, 2020
name: amys
title: Your basic American style yogurt
review: I decided to try making my own yogurt but didn't know where to start as far as cultures go, so I tried this first. The thickness and texture was pretty good if you like the standard store bought variety. I didn't like the tartness of this one though. I strained it twice which greatly improved it. That got rid of much of the tartness and created a super thick Greek style texture the first strain. Straining 2nd time created a rich cream cheese texture, so that was cool! I did not add anything to sweeten/flavor it so I will try it again in the future and it might be more appealing to make regularly. I wanted something different so Itried and fell in love with a Bulgarian culture so I have only been making that ever since. If you want something most Americans are used to (boring in my opinion) then this is it, but I would encourage you to explore beyond this basic variety. There are way better cultures waiting to excite your tastebuds!

title: Different Product than advertised and can't return
review: The individual packets in this product came as 3 gm packets NOT the 5 gram packets that are advertised. VERY disappointing AND these freeze dried packets are made with maltodextrin which is also not representative of the packaging that bought. The packaging listed on AMAZON nutrient facts does not list maltodextrin as an ingredient. I can't use maltodextrin. I tried to return this product and I cannot even though it's well within the general return window of AMAZON products. I'm not happy with this bate and switch!
